# V2 Data + Security Guardrails

Apply these rules for any data mutation scripts, SQL changes, or production-affecting updates.

## Before Any Data Mutation
- Always create a **before snapshot/backup** (temporary copy) first.
- Apply the change with the smallest possible scope (targeted rows/records only).
- Create an **after snapshot** and compare before/after results.
- Continue only if diffs match intended fields/rows.
- If verification fails, stop immediately and report unexpected changes.

## Mutation Safety
- Prefer guarded workflows (allowlists, scoped predicates, dry-runs).
- Never run blind bulk updates/deletes.
- Never run destructive commands without explicit user approval.
- Keep correction steps reversible where possible.

## Secrets and Access
- Never commit secrets (`.env`, service keys, tokens, credentials).
- Keep privileged keys server-side only; do not expose to client code.
- Use least-privilege credentials for automation/scripts.

## Auditability
- Log what changed, why, and how it was verified.
- Keep migration/backfill scripts idempotent when feasible.
- For approved financial data, avoid direct edits; use controlled correction flow.
